[{"id":35363,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["$20 \\mathrm{~m}$","$30 \\mathrm{~m}$","$40 \\mathrm{~m}$","$60 \\mathrm{~m}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\tan 30^{\\circ}=\\frac{h}{40+b}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\sqrt{3} h=40+b$\n$\\tan 60^{\\circ}=h / b \\Rightarrow h=\\sqrt{3} b$\n$\\Rightarrow b=20 m$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8908LxLh_SzHV8wbZr86un6eod_MDSVWRd2AdLRM5ZA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":35352,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math><mn>20</mn></math>","<math><mn>5</mn></math>","<math><mn>6</mn></math>","<math><mn>10</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/de8e7bfd-613c-4dfa-bf36-70a166e1b6c2-image.png\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 157px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&Delta;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mo>:</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>tan</mi><msup><mn>30</mn><mo>&deg;</mo></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></math> ......<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&Delta;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mo>:</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>tan</mi><msup><mn>60</mn><mo>&deg;</mo></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; ......<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math><br /><br />From equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&amp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo></math>&nbsp;we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>∵</mo></math> Speed is uniform<br /><br />Therefore, distance <math><mi>x</mi></math> walked by him in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>min</mi><mo>.</mo></math><br /><br />and distance <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> walked by him in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>min</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null},{"id":35327,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>From the given information in the question we can draw the following diagram</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a3c30d0f-bf05-4e9d-ba20-e30a02a442de-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 172px;\" /></p><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></math></p><p>So&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":35321,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given,</p><p>The angle of elevation of the top of a tower from a point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> due north of it is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi></math> and from a point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> at a distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp;units due west of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>13</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced></math>. If the distance of the point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> from the tower is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn></math> units, then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cot</mi><mi>&#945;</mi></math>&nbsp;is equal to</p><p>Now making the diagram of given value we have,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7abfce0b-98b5-4ca5-8ff3-fb510d75c6b0-image.png\" style=\"width: 338px; height: 250px;\" /></p><p>Given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>13</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now using the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#946;</mi></math>&nbsp;in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#9651;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;we get,&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/eaed5e41-ca93-4dd2-8def-f6805c72817f-551fbe22-619f-4236-9ac6-64ddc31cbca3-image.png\" style=\"width: 213px; height: 129px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>15</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mn>15</mn></mfrac></math>, so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p><p>Now in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#9651;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0632d039-1a94-4d71-9b56-7d372f9dd109-image.png\" style=\"width: 222px; height: 135px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>225</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>O</mi><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>81</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>225</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p><p>Now in triangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#9651;</mo><mi>O</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>P</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9103f87a-a646-4462-a79c-7b31da804210-image.png\" style=\"width: 219px; height: 130px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>cot</mi><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":35324,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given a vertical tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math> of height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></math> stands on a horizontal ground and from a point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> on the ground a man can see upto height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> of the tower with an angle of elevation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&alpha;</mi></math>. When from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>, he moves a distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> in the direction of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mo>&rarr;</mo></mover></math>, he can see the top <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;of the tower with an angle of elevation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&alpha;</mi></math>. If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>h</mi></math>, then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi></math>&nbsp;is equal to</p><p>Now on plotting the value in diagram we have,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/67fc22c4-8cf7-4624-aea5-ac002a8562b1-image.png\" style=\"width: 315px; height: 250px;\" />​​​​​​​</p><p>Now in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>△</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>△</mo><mi>H</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn><mi>h</mi></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>cot</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>h</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>from&nbsp;equation&nbsp;</mtext><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>tan</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&alpha;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Now put&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;on simplifying we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&rArr;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&alpha;</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":35337,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/58c3e582-7daf-4761-a40f-5585a5ea7270-image.png\" style=\"width: 291px; height: 281px;\" />&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mtext>and&#160;</mtext></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>400</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>200</mn><mi>PC</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>PC</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>400</mn></math>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":35362,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["$20 \\mathrm{~s}$","$1 \\mathrm{~s}$","$21 \\mathrm{~s}$","$24 \\mathrm{~s}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{1}{2} 2 t^2=21+20 t \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow t=21 .\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":35347,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["1500","750","720","1440"],"answer":3,"solution":"For $\\Delta \\mathrm{OA}, \\mathrm{A}, \\mathrm{OA}_1=\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{\\tan 60^{\\circ}}=1 \\mathrm{~km}$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/srRVPsDuSOrQGwaI--t9EcWDdiUOfhjzAfW8GowVJBw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nFor $\\Delta \\mathrm{OB}_1, \\mathrm{~B}, \\mathrm{OB}_1=\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{\\tan 30^{\\circ}}=3 \\mathrm{~km}$.\nAs, a distance of $3-1=2 \\mathrm{~km}$ is covered in 5 seconds. Therefore the speed of the plane is\n$$\n\\frac{2 \\times 3600}{5}=1440 \\mathrm{~km} / \\mathrm{hr}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":35329,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f3860b30-4114-4c0a-9e58-c386560273cb-image.png\" style=\"width: 214px; height: 238px;\" /></p><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></math>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>D</mi><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math></p><p>From Diagram</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#945;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8901;</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":35349,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>","<math><mn>100</mn></math>","<math><mn>50</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f6b37b60-80e6-4d11-9ee0-747f148b0a11-Untitled-tower.png\" style=\"width: 369px; height: 308px;\" />Let&nbsp;the height of the tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi></math> be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math></p><p>In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mo>&#8230;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>{</mo><mo>&#8757;</mo><mi>M</mi></math> is the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>}</mo></math></p><p>Now in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi><mi>P</mi></math>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8736;</mo><mi>N</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>(</mo><mo>&#8757;</mo></math> In a triangle sides opposite to equal angles are</p><p>equal<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math> )</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi></math></p><p>In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>Q</mi></math></p><p>By using Equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>200</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo></math> {By using Pythagoras theorem}</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> From <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>200</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>h</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>40000</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>40000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></math> {By squaring both the sides}</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>40000</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>10000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (08 Apr)","image":null},{"id":35326,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Plotting the diagram we get,</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ec310e5e-ab45-4f36-8cc2-8c00644ab13e-image.png\" style=\"width: 308px; height: 220px;\" /></p><p>In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>D</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>y</mi><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mi>ii</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>From equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;we get,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>tan</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>y</mi></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>y</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p><p>So, height of tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":35355,"subject":"Mathematics","chapter":"Heights and Distances","question":"","options":["$\\frac{260}{\\sqrt{37}}$","$\\frac{260}{37}$","$\\frac{80}{\\sqrt{37}}$","$\\frac{80}{37}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/YJYyJCG_i1zrnZWkQ5EkmN3Ji4cdWhoMmK6DjELGbO8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nLet $\\mathrm{OA}=x \\mathrm{~km}, \\mathrm{OB}=y \\mathrm{~km}, \\mathrm{AB}=\\mathrm{R}$ $(\\mathrm{AB})^2=(\\mathrm{OA})^2+(\\mathrm{OB})^2-2(\\mathrm{OA})(\\mathrm{OB}) \\cos$ $120^{\\circ}$\n$$\n\\mathrm{R}^2=x^2+y^2-2 x y\\left(-\\frac{1}{2}\\right)=x^2+y^2+x y\n$$\n$\\mathrm{R}$ at $x=6 \\mathrm{~km}$, and $y=8 \\mathrm{~km}$\n$$\n\\mathrm{R}=\\sqrt{6^2+8^2+6 \\times 8}=2 \\sqrt{37}\n$$\nDifferentiating equation (1) with respect to $t$\n$$\n\\begin{gathered}\n2 R \\frac{d R}{d t}=2 \\frac{d x}{d t}+2 y \\frac{d y}{d t}+\\left(x \\frac{d y}{d t}+y \\frac{d x}{d t}\\right) \\\\\n=\\frac{1}{2 R}[2 \\times 8 \\times 20+2 \\times 6 \\times 30+(8 \\times 30+6 \\times 20)] \\\\\n\\frac{d R}{d t}=\\frac{1}{2 \\times 2 \\sqrt{37}}[1040]=\\frac{260}{\\sqrt{37}}\n\\end{gathered}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (11 Apr Online)","image":null}]